">(Image credit: ilbusca/Getty Images)</span></figcaption></figure><p id=3D=
"1019ca26-9095-4c1e-aae9-a76bf13b2238">The Mersenne Primes are a class of n=
umbers that get big in a hurry.&nbsp; These prime numbers are equal to 2 ra=
ised to the power of a prime number minus 1. While the first few start out =
small =E2=80=94 3, 7, 31 =E2=80=94 they blow up to become incredibly large =
extremely quickly. Until about 1951, only 12 of these primes were known, bu=
t by this year (2024), 52 were known.</p><p>To power through these gigantic=
